< Review>
Used this place twice, a few years ago.

Jetski rental price is great.  Even with the lowest end jetski, 2 young men had fun on the 2-up.  Mission bay is fun.

Only issue is getting the watercraft to the water.  We had to use our truck (or theirs) to tow the jetski into the water.  There is a very close and large boat launch, just south of the place.

Not sure if they have a transport/towing service to bring the watercraft to water for you, but if they did they get more business.<//Review>

<Review>Overall a solid experience here. They provided me with the jetski and the truck to launch the jet ski myself. I was in and out in about 25-30 minutes (had to watch an orientation video,  fill out a form, then go over a safety brief/ inspection of the jetski). The price is really fair for what you get. < Review>
ABSOLUTE CROOKS. My friend and I were on vacation and decided we would rent a jet ski for the day.  We called and reserved a jet ski for the day.  On the phone we found out that we have to put the jet ski in the water ourselves and take it out.  They told us if we didn't have a vehicle to tow it, they had loaner vehicles available.  We thought this was very unconventional, but we went along with it.  When we got there we had to wait for the guy to finish with the people before us.  Then they showed us a safety video and went over how to put the jet ski in and out of the water.  They then had us look over the jet ski and told us that everything that has white tape over it, they know about and is ok.  Anything with silver marker on it is ok and they know about it.  Any other damage you find that you can find that can catch with your fingernail you need to inform them of.  We looked it over and found a few scratches that we showed them.  Since we were just visiting the city for a short amount of time, we didn't have rental car, so we used a loaner truck.  Just as we were getting in the truck, they asked if we had a place to put the gas can of spare gas for the jet ski when we got there and we said no, just the truck, and that's when they told us that after we put the jet ski in the bay, we need to bring them the truck and trailer back and then walk back to the bay.  Then after we were done jet skiing, we would have to walk back to the rental place to pick up the truck and trailer and drive it back to the bay and pick up the jet ski and take it back.  Now the walk was only a 10-15 minute walk, but still inconvenient.  We had fun on the jet ski, aside from the intake continuously clogging with very little seaweed and requiring clean out.  The jet skis speedometer also did not work, which they said they already knew and had just neglected to tell us.  When we were finished riding we walked back, got the truck and trailer, and took the jet ski back.  They then inspected it and filled it back up with gas, that we were charged for!  Your rental fee does not include any gas!  At this point we had paid $250 for the rental, and $37.50 for gas.  Then they said, "well it looks like your all set, except for some damage back here."  Our heads immediately shot up because we didn't know of any damage.  We hadn't hit anything or been hit by anything on the water, and it was a cloudy day so aside from 2 other jet skiers that we never crossed paths with, we were alone on the water.  They showed us a crack in the fiberglass on the side in the back right before the back corner of the platform that you board the jet ski from.  He said it needed repair because it was taking on water.  The only problem was, THE CRACK WAS LINKED TO PRE-EXITING DAMAGE!!!  I saw the 2 cracks disappeared underneath a piece of tape, and said those aren't our fault, they are connected to these cracks under this piece of tape that you said was fine.  They then peeled back the tape and the cracks we were accused of were part of the cracks under the tape.  The cracks didn't even like just like make a turn and connect to the original ones, they were fluent right off the end of the ones covered by the tape.  They were not separate cracks, they were the same crack!!!  They said we need to show the owner.  They then said that this crack in the fiber glass wouldn't have just spread, it would have required a strike by something or that we had to have done something to it.  There was no evidence of anything hitting it.  I told them that it probably cracked more because it is the side of the boarding platform, and us getting on and off of the jet ski would have put pressure there and that might cause the crack to expand, but it is from pre-existing damage. We cant help that.  They then said since it is liked to pre-exiting damage, we are only going to be charged a quarter of the repair cost which is $100.00  That is ridiculous!  We shouldn't have to pay anything for a crack that they knew existed when it left! We will never go back to this establishment and neither should you.</Review>

< text>
We were here for lunch (6 perspns). We recommend this place. The amount of salt, fat and sugar in the food had good balance. The staff were very helpful and kind.

Pad Thai, with extra vegetables. Tom yum soup. Vegetable curry, Red snapper with veggies. Vegetarian spicy basil and Beef and broccoli are traditional Thai food you can eat here.

The reason for why not 5 stars is because they gathered/kept all the plates, glasses, leftovers foods and utensils that they clean from the tables - just next to our table which was no a good sight and experience to see.<//text>

< Name>
Nikki Beller< /Name>
<time>1559240441432</time>< rating>
1</rating>
< Review>
I'm working from home today, because I am still sick from the food I ordered from Chana Thai last night.

What kind of greasy, bland, overcooked, diarrhea inducing mess was that, Chana Thai?   I have only ever had one food delivery experience worse than this one  - and that was when an UberEats driver backed me in to a corner and screamed in my face.

I've ordered from here once before - the food was just okay.  Nothing notably good or bad; but delivery was free and timely, and the food was edible.  Last night I placed an order around 8:10 pm.  They close at 9:30  maybe it was too late?   Delivery was supposed to take 45 - 60 minutes.  It took nearly 90.  That's fine.  Sometimes things take longer than expected.  The one-star review is, not for the food that was 30 minutes late.  It is not for the fact that the restaurant didn't even acknowledge the fact that I waited so long.

I went to bed still hangry (hungry / angry)  because the food that arrived was simply awful.  The tom yum soup, which I ordered medium, and got with not spice at all,  seemed to be missing the lemongrass - normally the prevailing note in Tom Yum soup -  so it just tasted like murky broth with boiled chicken and mushrooms.  Pad Won Sen was awful. I ordered spicy and there was zero spice in the dish, but two small containers of chili sauce in the bag.  I guess its "DIY" spicy.  Those noodles were an overcooked gloppy, mess, at once falling apart and stuck together in clumps, and swimming in an Exxon Valdez level oil slick.  The were at once bland and horribly over salted.  The only other flavor seemed to be too much acrid garlic  (and I actually love garlic), and a heavy dose of MSG.  I had to throw this food out.  I went to bed hungry, mad, with a gasoline-like after taste, stank breath that was no match for toothpaste and mouthwash, and an MSG headache  (I'm mildly allergic to MSG).  I woke up, and realized I need to spend most of the day near the restroom, while this abomination that was called food works its way out of my system.

#NeverAgain  #Hangry< /Review>

< text>
Not your typical Inglewood restaurant. Maybe, it is the cuisine. I love Thai dishes, and I was looking for another Asian spot nearby, but saw the word, "Thai," and I had to try it. The interior is beautifully decorated, and the food is simply great. I had the vegetables in teriyaki sauce, the sauce was a tad sweet, but may taste a little better with rice. In couldn't eat any rice, the rest of my daily meals are all high in fiber. I didn't want to feel bloated after lunch. Good choices for meat eaters, or vegetarians-I'm a veggie.< /text>

<Date>1398296040837< /Date><username>Pamela Perez</username><Review>Delivery was quick. I liked the way the veggies were cut, there was love put into them.

Kee Mow (spicy noodles)~ were well cooked,  edible, just needed a bit more mint flavor and I'd gave it all a 5star.. Definitely two persons could split the plate.

Tom Kha Soup~ was delicious

<username>Isidro Perez</username><Date>1500231160838</Date><rate>4< /rate>< review>
Overall experience was very positive but with a twist.

Purchased 4 tires from this American Tire Depot after the fiasco with the American Tire Depot 2 on McHenry. Originally had a appointment to get the new tires installed on saturday and decided to see if i could get them installed on friday instead. Called around 12pm and the gentleman at the counter told me he could get me in if i got there before 5:30pm. Said thanks and left work early. Got there around 4:45pm. Guy at the counter for some reason knew who i was. Acknowledged that i had some issues with the one on McHenry. (Still dont know how he knew as i never told him.) Guy was very helpful and always addressed me by my first name which is rare now a days. Got me started on my tire install at around 5:15 pm or so. They started to work on my car and get the tires installed when the unthinkable happened. They sent 1 wrong tire of the 4 i had asked for.  As it is i have strange tires on my fiat (told over and over again by all the tire places).  Dillian (i hope thats his name) calls me over and said they have an issue they sent one wrong tire. I was like Nooooo... (was over exaggerating but was a little mad) Dillian (let me know ill edit this post) was very professional and said ill take care of you ill call right now and have them send me a tire in the morning. At first i was upset but as he was very professional, never lost his cool and apologized i said all right ill come back in the morning.

Also on a side note when i was there there was a hispanic gentleman talking to my wife in the waiting area. The elderly man was talking to her and was saying that they are very busy here and that he wasn't sure if he was going to be able to get his tire worked on or not. I was in the garage area and i swear to you Dillian was working on a tire and all of a sudden stopped what he was doing walked to the door to the waiting area and said dont worry sir i didn't forget about you ill get you fixed up shortly. He walked back out the the garage and went right back to helping his crew.

My wife on saturday told me that the guy had like super hearing or something because after the the elderly man told her about them helping him or not that's when dillan came back and reassured him. She was kinda freaked out and told the elderly man in spanish they have mics up in here or something as how would he know what we were talking about in spanish.?!?!?! ( Spider senses with a helping of google translate lol)

Saturday comes along and i call around 11am and before i can even tell him who i am he tells me. Come on in your tire is here. I was like wow ok cool be there in a few. Get there and as i am walking in he is walking out to get the keys and pulls it up to get it serviced. Last tire is installed and he tells me to come back every 5k miles for tire rotations.

Overall great service and good tire rates.</review>

<Rate>5</Rate><Review>I am so glad that I went to this store. I am from Louisiana and have been working in Modesto with no family here. I had just purshaced 4 tires for my lil Honda Civic SI at Costo, hit a low curb and blew both tires out on the passanger side. To my horror these tires were on back order and were not compatible with any other type tires. I searched everywhere for 2 more to match with the 2 good ones with no luck. In the mean time my full coverage insurance did not cover for a rental car. I went to this store and it was finally explained to me why my tires were so hard to match. They were directional tires. The guys here explained to me in detail about the difference between directional and nondirectional tires. I was given a quote on 4 new tires that were nondirectional as I had decided that in case I had a blow out again I would have the same problem if I stayed with the directional tires. However with the nondirectional tires I would be able to easily replace the damaged tire. I was quoted a price on 4 high end Michelin tires and got a$ 70.00 rebate off them as well. The guys told me to let them know if anyone beat their price and they would go even lower in price on these tires. I spent the next day shopping around and even went back to Costco for quotes on the tires trying to beat their price. I was not successful so I went back to the Tier Depot and got my 4 tires for better than 200.00 what everyone else wanted. I got the best price, customer service and respect from these fellas at The American Tire Drpot on Prescott in Modesto CA. I will Let all of my friends that I know here to go to them as I believe they are honest, hardworking  guys who will stand by their product. < review>
I've been a member here for about 2 weeks now. This is the best gym that I've been to in LA. Small but they have more than most large chain gyms. Staff if very friendly and will learn to know you by name. Their equipment focuses on muscle building which is perfect for me. The cardio equipment from Nordictrack is actually making me enjoy cardio while watching Netflix. I've tried some of the big gyms and after paying the same price that I pay here, the only thing I flelt was frustrated because of the how crowded places like LA fitness are. There, no one re-rackes their weights or cares that there's 7 people waiting to use the bench that some guy is on his phone texting on. If you're looking for a friendly environment to workout where you won't have to wait in line for your equipment, where you get treated like an actual member and not just another face.... Look no further because bishoys gym is it.</review>

<Rate>5<//Rate><text>Its hard to say anything that hasn't already been said about Bishoy's Gym...  So I'll tell my story and why I joined:

I view finding a gym the same way you would when you're trying to find a new barber or hairstylist... you know when you find a good one, you're going to stick with it and be with them for sometime so you better vet them well.

I'm a 42 year old dad, with a "dad bod", of course like many men I worked out plenty in my teens and 20s, then life and poor workout habits and injuries and fatherhood got in the way.  I took years off and am now ready to get back into some good lifting but with the wisdom of my years and not the reckless abandon of being young and thinking my body is invincible, LOL.

I just moved to LA and was looking for a gym, of course checked out the standards like LA Fitness and 24 Hour Fitness and was disgusted by their sales tactics and generally un-knowledgable staff members.  Yes, those places were closer to me and more convenient, but I just couldn't bring myself to make a long term commitment to them because of their business model.  Was driving past Bishoy's on Pico and thought, "hmm, maybe that place has potential"

I called and made an appt with Bishoy to check the place out and wow, what a treasure.  Yes, its small, but if you want a good solid place to work out with CLEAN, and TOP OF THE LINE equipment... this is your place.  Not only that, but to reiterate what others have said, Bishoy is a great guy who takes care of his members and takes pride in his gym.

I'm really, really happy that I found a great place to workout and at the same time I get to support a business who is really doing it right.

Kudos to Bishoy and doing business right in this day and age!< /text><Pictures>None</Pictures>< response>

James J. Griffin< /name>
<Text>We have dinner at Cool Hand Luke's almost every time I visit my Grandpa. I really like the old west vibe they have going on. It's a rather spacious restaurant so there's rarely a time they can't immediately accommodate a party of four. More than that and you should make a reservation, but the back room easily handled our party of fifteen.

The food is hearty. I had a 9oz New York strip last night and it was seasoned to perfection. I had a side of mashed potatoes which left the plate looking a little colorless, but that's my fault. I should have gone with the mixed veggies.

Their drink menu is eclectic and has quite a few strong mixed punches for the connoisseur of brightly colored sweet cocktails that will knock you on your ass. Think long island but blue, pink or whatever.

The tap list is pretty good and the happy hour bar is welcoming. Getting across College Ave is a bit of a pain during rush hour if you're coming from the 101 south, but other than that there's not any logistical issues.< /Text>< Gmap_id>

< review>
I ordered to petite bacon-wrapped filets, medium rare. They came out to me medium well. They brought me to new steaks which tasted bland and they had a gray pallor.and one of the steaks, I found a rather large wooden skewer that was broken off in the steak, I was lucky I didn't bite into it. The whiskey peppercorn sauce that was supposed to come with the steaks, had more of a consistency of a lumpy gravy and tasted only of salt. The bloomin Onion that we ordered as an appetizer, was lukewarm to say the least and not crunchy at all. We also noticed, that the appetizer came out very quickly, as if it had already been made and was sitting there on a counter somewhere in the kitchen. The coffee that my friend ordered was bitter and I could tell that it was old coffee. Don't waste your time or money coming to this place. Well Cool hand Luke's in Santa Maria used to be very good, it has definitely gone downhill.<//review>

< Text>
Would have given it 4.5 stars if I could. I had the Whiskey Skillet steak with Bleu cheese added and a side of calamari and beef stew. The steak and stew were absolutely excellent; the calamari very good. The steak was ordered medium rare, but was cooked slightly closer to medium. Still excellent. Calamari was a tad on the chewy side, but definitely better than most. The whiskey sauce was served on the side as it should be, not on the steak and it was delicious. Service was prompt and attentive, but not overbearing. All in all, I give the steak a recommended must have, and the calamari recommended.< /Text>

< Text>
Only average overall. Ordered Lukes western ribeye with the green beans and salad. Asked for medium rare, came medium well, very little pink at all. Somewhat tough and grissely on the cut.
The sauteed nushrooms and roasted garlic were excellent but not enough so to make up for the steak I only ate 1/2 of. Green beans side was also excellent, possibly sauteed in the mushroom butter. And the salad was only average, with watered down bleu cheese dressing.
Service was acceptable but not extra attentive, and since when does a restaurant not provide silverware by default? We had to ask for every piece of silverware individually.
Sad to say that even though the vegetables were great, I probably will not go back, and will choose the local non-franchise steak house instead.< /Text>

<response>None<//response><Pictures>None</Pictures><text>We've been here three times and have left very satisfied after all three meals. Yes, it IS pricier than McDonald's or In & Out Burger, and that is because this is a top-notch steakhouse. Your steak is cooked to order, your fish is perfectly flaked, your calimari isn't too chewy or underdone. The lettuce in the salad could be fresher, but because of the amount that they serve daily, that would be impossible--they have to use bagged lettuce, like most every other restaurant. The beans you get to start your meal are hot and seasoned perfectly, as is your steak, chicken or fish, or even your burger (if that's how you roll.) We have not made it to dessert, not because it probably isn't great, like everything else, but just because we don't have room for it. We don't drink alcohol, but the tea is always fresh and the Coke is never flat or too carbonated. Hands down, my favorite place to eat a T-bone in central California.< /text><Rating>4<//Rating><date>1485072172451<//date>< Gmap_id>
